{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"08ae7e31-dc38-4e38-9fcd-8a2a3fcf64ae","content":"No files found in the workspace — this is a general guidance question. Here's exactly what to do:\n\n### 1. Add `x:DataType` to your XAML\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout>\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize}\" />\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe key change is adding `xmlns:vm` and `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"`. All `{Binding}` expressions under that scope are now **compiled** — the compiler resolves property names against `SettingsViewModel` at build time.\n\n### 2. Catch binding errors at build time\n\nCompiled bindings already produce **build errors** (not runtime failures) when a property name is wrong. To make this even stricter across the whole project, add this to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n    <!-- Treat binding failures as compile errors (net9.0+) -->\n    <MauiStrictXamlCompilation>true</MauiStrictXamlCompilation>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### Key rules to remember\n\n| Scenario | What to do |\n|---|---|\n| Property typo (e.g., `{Binding Themee}`) | Compiler error — caught automatically |\n| Binding inside a `DataTemplate` | Add `x:DataType` on the template root too |\n| Need to opt out for one binding | Use `x:DataType=\"\"` locally to disable |\n| Mixed binding contexts (e.g., parent ref) | Use `Source=` with `x:DataType` on that binding |\n\nThat's it — `x:DataType` is the only XAML change needed. Your existing `{Binding ...}` syntax stays the same; the compiler just validates it now.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2a260078-19ee-494f-ba39-22590fdaa25c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"No files found. The user is asking a conceptual question about how to convert a MAUI page to use compiled bindings. Let me provide the answer directly.","outputTokens":595,"requestId":"9820:155537:165D1D1:18E376D:6A051DAA"},"id":"52da431e-22a2-4174-92d5-b4f6bb6d0228","timestamp":"2026-05-14T00:56:25.499Z","parentId":"67992eda-b271-411a-9726-475731540bac"}
